This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on the performance of contextualised word embedding ELMo models in word sense disambiguation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves training and evaluating machine learning models, which suggests that it could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the linguistic nature of languages, which could make it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
